    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence labeling for Plexin B1 and PSD-95 (DLG4) in cultured hippocampal neurons showed postsynaptic localization.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: \"Hippocampal neurons were cultured as described by Banker and Goslin [2] with modifications. In brief, the hippocampal tissues were dissociated from Sprague-Dawley rat embryos of embryonic day 18 (E18) (SLC),\"\n\nantibody:\n\"Polyclonal antibodies to plexin-B1 were raised by immunizing rabbits with maltose binding protein (MBP)-fused-mouse plexin-B1 (amino acid, 1216-1521, NM_17725). The specificity of the antibodies was confirmed by Western blot analysis.\"",
